Simple Artichoke dip (one of my faves):
1 can finely chopped artichokes (not marinated) hint-a food processor is great for this.
1 cup Mayonnaise
1 cup Grated Parmesan cheese
Pinch of dill (if you want)
Bake for about 25 min or until bubbly. You can obviously add some spinach if you'd like.

Zoe was talking about artichoke dip, so I thought I would share my favorite recipe:


1 can artichoke hearts (not marinated)
1/2 c mayo
1/3 c shredded mozzarella
1/8 cup shredded parmesan
Minced garlic to taste (I use a lot!)


Drain and coarsely chop artichokes. Mix all ingredients together. Bake in a serving dish at 350F for 40-45 minutes. Easy and delicious!
